Ques:-

The Nautilus Development Team recently deployed a new web application hosted on an EC2 instance within a public VPC named devops-vpc. The application, running on an Nginx server, should be accessible from the internet on port 80. Despite configuring the security group devops-sg to allow traffic on port 80 and verifying the EC2 instance settings, the application remains inaccessible from the internet. The team suspects that the issue might be related to the VPC configuration, as all other components appear to be set up correctly. The DevOps team has been asked to troubleshoot and resolve the issue to ensure the application is accessible to external users.

As a member of the Nautilus DevOps Team, your task is to perform the following:

1. Verify VPC Configuration: Ensure that the VPC devops-vpc is properly configured to allow internet access.

2. Ensure Accessibility: Make sure the EC2 instance devops-ec2 running the Nginx server is accessible from the internet on port 80.




Soln:-

Step 1: Describe the VPC

aws ec2 describe-vpcs \
  --query "Vpcs[*].{ID:VpcId,CIDR:CidrBlock,Name:Tags[?Key=='Name']|[0].Value}" \
  --output table



Step 2: Verify VPC has an Internet Gateway

aws ec2 describe-internet-gateways --filters "Name=attachment.vpc-id,Values=<vpc-id>"



Step 3: Verify the Internet Gateway

aws ec2 describe-internet-gateways --internet-gateway-ids <internet-gateway-id>



Step 4: Attach the Internet Gateway to your VPC

aws ec2 attach-internet-gateway \
  --internet-gateway-id <internet-gateway-id> \
  --vpc-id <vpc-id>



Step 5: Repair the Route Table so the default route points to the IGW

aws ec2 replace-route \
  --route-table-id <route-table-id> \
  --destination-cidr-block 0.0.0.0/0 \
  --gateway-id <internet-gateway-id>



Step 6: Verify Route Table has a default route to the Internet Gateway

aws ec2 describe-route-tables --filters "Name=vpc-id,Values=<vpc-id>"



Step 7: Verify EC2 Instance Public IP

aws ec2 describe-instances \
  --filters "Name=tag:Name,Values=devops-ec2" \
  --query "Reservations[*].Instances[*].PublicIpAddress" \
  --output text



Step 8: Generate EIP:

aws ec2 allocate-address --domain vpc



Step 9: Attach EIP to EC2 instance

aws ec2 associate-address --instance-id <instance-id> --allocation-id <eipalloc-id>



Step 10: Get all the Secuity Groups in a VPC

aws ec2 describe-security-groups \
  --filters "Name=vpc-id,Values=<vpc-id>" \
  --query "SecurityGroups[*].{ID:GroupId,Name:GroupName}" \
  --output table
  


Step 11: Describe a Security Group for ports verification if allow or not

aws ec2 describe-security-groups --group-ids <sg-id>

if port 80 is not allowed. Then use the below command:
aws ec2 authorize-security-group-ingress \
  --group-id <sg-id> \
  --protocol tcp \
  --port 80 \
  --cidr 0.0.0.0/0



Step 12: Describe Public IP of the Ec2 Instance

aws ec2 describe-instances --filters "Name=tag:Name,Values=devops-ec2" --query "Reservations[*].Instances[*].PublicIpAddress" --output text



Step 13: Test (it should visible the nginx welcome page)

curl -v http://<public-ip-of-Ec2>

